Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a light-brown pottery storage-vessel, the fabric is partially grey in section, the exterior is covered with self-slip and remains of two lines of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393758) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393758)
